      {
        "header": "Justification and Support",
        "description": "Justification for the project, its local impact, and existing support or co-submissions.",
        "fields": [
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_1929176826:1a2676b12314",
            "label": "Please provide a brief summary and justification of your request:",
            "help_text": "Do not include specific entity names in this field.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Requesting $9 billion for the NASA Science Mission Directorate (SMD) to maintain U.S. preeminence in space exploration and ensure the stability of the high-tech workforce.\n* SMD programs drive economic growth, with every $1 invested returning roughly $3 to the economy while addressing peer competition in space from China.\n* Funding supports the implementation of National Academies' Decadal Surveys, which provide the nonpartisan, peer-reviewed roadmap for major scientific breakthroughs.",
            "rationale": "The summary draws on the $9B ask amount and core advocacy talking points regarding economic return, Chinese competition, and Decadal Survey priorities while following the instruction to exclude specific entity names.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_2110127992:fa25a1698d00",
            "label": "Additional Background",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* In FY2026, Congress demonstrated strong bipartisan support for NASA Science by restoring funding after significant proposed cuts to prevent the loss of critical technical capabilities.\n* Consistent and predictable funding is essential to avoid further disruption to the aerospace supply chain and to retain the specialized civil servant and contractor workforce.\n* This $9 billion request provides the necessary resources to restore momentum for key missions and maintain the talent pipeline for the broader technology economy.",
            "rationale": "Uses background on the FY2026 funding restoration and workforce stability arguments from the advocacy context to provide additional justification.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_2050022848:0101f0d9fdd8",
            "label": "How will this request benefit the State?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science has directly invested $203,246 in the district through recent grant funding to the University of Texas at Tyler for advanced research.\n* District-level funding supports innovative projects like developing sensors for real-time plant stress analysis, advancing agricultural and biological technology.\n* Federal investment in NASA Science strengthens the STEM talent pipeline in Texas, ensuring students and entrepreneurs remain at the forefront of the aerospace and technology sectors.",
            "rationale": "Directly cites the $203,246 local spending data and the specific grant to the University of Texas at Tyler for sensor development.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_85605933:f9a33ba18a57",
            "label": "Please provide any Members, Senators, or other organizations you have submitted to or who supports this request:",
